:R-HSA-450385  a            obo:GO_0043488 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "Butyrate Response Factor 1 (BRF1, ZFP36L1, not to be confused with transcription factor IIIB) binds AU-rich elements in the 3' region of mRNAs. After binding, BRF1 recruits exonucleases (XRN1 and the exosome) and decapping enzymes (DCP1a and DCP2) to hydrolyze the RNA. The ability of BRF1 to direct RNA degradation is controlled by phosphorylation of BRF1. Protein kinase B/AKT1 phosphorylates BRF1 at serines 92 and 203. Phosphorylated BRF1 can still bind RNA but is sequestered by binding 14-3-3 protein, preventing BRF1 from destabilizing RNA. BRF1 is also phosphorylated by MK2 at serines 54, 92, 203, and at an unknown site in the C-terminus. It is unknown if this particular phosphorylated form of BRF1 binds 14-3-3." ;
        rdfs:label          "Butyrate Response Factor 1 (BRF1) binds and destabilizes mRNA" ;
        dc:contributor      "Authored: May, B, 2009-12-29" , "Edited: May, B, 2009-12-29" , "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Wilusz, J, 2010-06-29" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-450385" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-450531/R-HSA-450531> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

<http://identifiers.org/uniprot/P49137>
